var __index = {"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"],"fields":{"title":{"boost":1000.0},"text":{"boost":1.0},"tags":{"boost":1000000.0}}},"docs":[{"location":"index.html","title":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83c\udf73 Family Cookbook","text":""},{"location":"index.html#whats-inside","title":"\u2728 What\u2019s Inside","text":"<p>Browse through our recipe categories to find your next favorite dish:</p> <ul> <li>\u2600\ufe0f Breakfast </li> <li>\ud83e\udd63 Soups</li> <li>\ud83c\udf72 Big Meals</li> <li>\ud83e\udd57 Salads &amp; Dressings</li> <li>\ud83c\udf74 Savoury</li> <li>\ud83c\udf70 Sweets</li> </ul> <p>\ud83d\udd17 Online Version: gerald1248.github.io/cookbook/</p> <p>\ud83d\udc19 GitHub Repository: github.com/gerald1248/cookbook</p>"},{"location":"big_meals/bolognese.html","title":"\ud83c\udf5d Bolognese","text":""},{"location":"big_meals/bolognese.html#ingredients","title":"\ud83d\uded2 Ingredients","text":"<p>1 Tbsp olive oil 500g (red) onions, finely minced 6 cloves of garlic 120g celery, finely minced  120g carrots, finely minced 120g optional: courgette / red pepper, finely minced 1 tsp olive oil  400g mushrooms, finely minced 750g soya mince (frozen, Linda McCartney) 1 Tbs yeast extract 2 Tbs soya sauce / tamari 2 tsp (smoked) salt 4 tins chopped tomatoes 1 bay leave 2 Tbs tomato pur\u00e9e  1 Tbsp sugar 1(?) tsp salt (season to taste w salt after cooking)</p>"},{"location":"big_meals/bolognese.html#method","title":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83c\udf73 Method","text":"<p>Fry onions in olive oil until ever so slightly browned. Add garlic for 1 minute in the end. Fry veggies for 3 minutes. Transfer to slow cooker. Add the tsp of olive oil then fry mushrooms until all water has evaporated. Add soya mince and continue frying until defrosted and slightly fried. Season with yeast extract, soya sauce and smoked salt. Mix thoroughly. Transfer to the slow cooker. Pour tinned tomatoes in the pot used for frying and mash with a masher before adding them to the slow cooker. Add tomato pur\u00e9e and sugar, mix thoroughly. Hide bay leave near the centre.</p> <p>Cook on high for 5h.</p> <p>Season with salt / black pepper to taste after cooking.</p>"},{"location":"big_meals/cajun-kidney-beans.html","title":"Cajun kidney beans","text":""},{"location":"big_meals/cajun-kidney-beans.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>1Tbs oil 400g minced red onions 30g minced garlic 2 Tbs Cajun spice mix (M&amp;S) 400g finely minced green peppers 400g finely minced celery (peeled on the outside) 10 tins Kidney beans (drained and rinsed) 2 bay leaves 450ml veg broth 3.5 tsp smoked salt / salt 2 tsp dark brown sugar 3 Tbs lime juice</p>"},{"location":"big_meals/cajun-kidney-beans.html#method","title":"Method","text":"<ul> <li>Fry onions until browned</li> <li>Add garlic and spices and fry some more</li> <li>Add everything to the slow cooker cook on high (hours) or on low (hours)</li> <li>Mash about half the kidney beans, just inside the slow cooker.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"big_meals/italian-tofu-meatballs.html","title":"Italian tofu meatballs","text":""},{"location":"big_meals/italian-tofu-meatballs.html#preparation-time","title":"Preparation time","text":"<p>30 minutes</p>"},{"location":"big_meals/italian-tofu-meatballs.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>1 (14 ounce) package extra-firm tofu</p> <p>1 onion, chopped</p> <p>1 egg</p> <p>\u00bd cup bread crumbs</p> <p>\u00bd cup grated Parmesan cheese</p> <p>1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce</p> <p>1 \u00bc teaspoons chopped fresh basil</p> <p>1 \u00bc teaspoons chopped fresh marjoram</p> <p>1 \u00bc teaspoons chopped fresh rosemary</p> <p>1 \u00bc teaspoons chopped fresh oregano</p> <p>1 \u00bc teaspoons chopped fresh thyme</p> <p>1 teaspoon red pepper flakes</p> <p>1 teaspoon salt</p> <p>\u00bd teaspoon hot sauce</p> <p>\u00bd teaspoon minced garlic</p> <p>\u00bc cup olive oil</p>"},{"location":"big_meals/italian-tofu-meatballs.html#method","title":"Method","text":"<p>Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil.</p> <p>Place tofu onto a plate and place another plate on top. Set a 3- to 5-pound weight on top. Press tofu for 15 minutes to drain excess water. Break tofu into small pieces and squeeze again to remove as much water as possible.</p> <p>Place tofu in a large bowl. Add onion, egg, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, Worcestershire sauce, basil, marjoram, rosemary, oregano, thyme, red pepper flakes, salt, hot sauce, and garlic; mix well with your hands until thoroughly combined.</p> <p>Drizzle some olive oil on the lined baking sheet. Form tablespoonfuls of tofu mixture into balls and arrange in rows on the baking sheet. Drizzle remaining olive oil over meatballs.</p> <p>Bake in the preheated oven until browned and firm to the touch, 25 to 30 minutes.</p>"},{"location":"big_meals/soya-burgers.html","title":"Soya burgers","text":""},{"location":"big_meals/soya-burgers.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>210g soya mince, finely minced (eg Linda McCartney frozen) * 70g onions, finely minced almost pur\u00e9ed  1 tsp garlic, finely minced almost pur\u00e9ed 1 tsp Dijon mustard 1 tsp ketchup / tomato pur\u00e9e  2 Tbs flat leaved parsley, finely minced 1.5 Tbs chickpea flower **</p> <p>* (try adding finely minced and fried mushrooms) ** (try poha thick rice flakes instead or a mix)</p>"},{"location":"big_meals/soya-burgers.html#method","title":"Method","text":"<p>Mix all ingredients, form patties and let them cool in the fridge.</p>"},{"location":"big_meals/tomato-sauce.html","title":"Tomato sauce creamy with vegetables","text":""},{"location":"big_meals/tomato-sauce.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>1-2 Tbs olive oil 200g onions, chopped  1-2 Tbsp garlic, minced 100-200g vegetables, minced (carrot and celery or courgette / sweet peppers)kkk 2 tins chopped tomatoes  6 sundried tomatoes, chopped  2 tsp sugar  1.5 tsp salt</p>"},{"location":"big_meals/tomato-sauce.html#method","title":"Method","text":"<p>Fry onions in olive oil until ever so slightly browned. Add garlic and veggies for 2 mins, stir a few times. Pour in tinned tomatoes and sundried tomatoes. Let simmer for 30-60mins. Transfer to a high speed blender and blend smooth. Season with 1.5 tsp salt and 2 tsp sugar.</p> <p>For creaminess add cashews and water 2:1 for the high speed blender step.</p>"},{"location":"breakfast/baked-granola.html","title":"Baked granola","text":""},{"location":"breakfast/baked-granola.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>500g big oats 70g coconut oil 90g golden sirup 2 Tbs vanilla extract  2 tsp cinnamon  1/2 tsp salt </p> <p>Stir while pouring in the melted oil and sirup.</p> <p>Bake at 150-160C for 40 mins. Stir halfway through, after 20 mins. Bake in 2cm layer.</p>"},{"location":"breakfast/courgette-fritters.html","title":"Courgette fritters","text":""},{"location":"breakfast/courgette-fritters.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>500g courgettes, grated 2tsp fine salt 2tsp onion powder  2tsp onion granules  1 heaped Tbsp gram flour + 3Tbsp warm water (replaces 1 eggs) 30g potato starch 25g oat flour</p>"},{"location":"breakfast/courgette-fritters.html#method","title":"Method","text":"<p>Grate courgettes. Mix w 2 tsp fine salt. Transfer mix to fine sieve and place sieve over bowl. Let liquid drain, push liquid out w a large spoon and applying pressure. Once most liquid has drained, tip out liquid and put grated and salted courgettes back in the bowl.</p> <p>Add gram egg. Mix well. Mix onion powder, granules, potato starch and  oat flour. Add the dry mix to the bowl. Mix some more and let rest for 15 mins.</p> <p>Fry in small portions (slightly heaped Tbsp) from both sides medium heat</p>"},{"location":"breakfast/pancakes.html","title":"\ud83e\udd5e Pancakes thin / thick","text":""},{"location":"breakfast/pancakes.html#ingredients","title":"\ud83d\uded2 Ingredients","text":"<p>210g white flour 70g wholegrain flour (optional, can be replaced w 80g white flour) 1.5 / 2.5 tsp baking powder (thin / thick) 1 tsp vanilla extract  28g melted butter / neutral oil (if using wholegrain flour, otherwise optional) 60g sugar 470 / 600ml (soy) milk (thick / thin)</p>"},{"location":"breakfast/pancakes.html#method","title":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83c\udf73 Method","text":"<p>Mix dry ingredients. Add 330ml soy milk and mix, this is it avoid clumps. Add remaining milk (140ml for thick, 270ml for thin). Add vanilla extract and melted butter / oil. Stir carefully. Let batter rest for 5-10 mins. </p> <p>Heat frying pan. Add thin coating of oil w silicon brush. Add pancake batter and tilt the pan to make thinner pancakes.</p>"},{"location":"breakfast/potato-fritters.html","title":"Potato Fritters","text":""},{"location":"breakfast/potato-fritters.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>750g potatoes, grated 2tsp fine salt 2tsp onion powder  2tsp onion granules  3 heaped Tbsp gram flour + 9Tbsp warm water (replaces 3 eggs) 35g oat flour</p>"},{"location":"breakfast/potato-fritters.html#method","title":"Method","text":"<p>Grate potatoes. Mix w 2 tsp fine salt. Transfer mix to fine sieve and place sieve over bowl. Let liquid drain, push liquid out w a large spoon and applying pressure. Once most liquid has drained, tip out liquid and put grated and salted potatoes back in the bowl.</p> <p>Add onion powder and granules plus gram eggs. Mix well. Add oat flour. Mix some more and let rest for 15 mins. Fry in small portions (slightly heaped Tbsp) from both sides medium heat</p>"},{"location":"breakfast/wunderbroed.html","title":"Wunderbroed Scandinavian Bread","text":""},{"location":"breakfast/wunderbroed.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>Psyllium husk</p> <p>Oats</p> <p>Gluten free bread</p>"},{"location":"salad/mustard-dressing.html","title":"Mayonnaise Mustard Dressing","text":""},{"location":"salad/mustard-dressing.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>100g mayonnaise, vegan Hellmann\u2019s</p> <p>100g / ml soya milk</p> <p>10g Dijon mustard, Maille</p> <p>8g salt</p>"},{"location":"salad/mustard-dressing.html#method","title":"Method","text":"<p>Put all ingredients into a jar with a lid and shake or mix them in a bowl / glass with a fork.</p>"},{"location":"savoury/kidney-bean-leberwurst-vegan.html","title":"Kidney Bean Smoked Tofu Leberwurst Vegan","text":""},{"location":"savoury/kidney-bean-leberwurst-vegan.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>1 can kidney beans, 240g drained weight</p> <p>150g smoked tofu</p> <p>1 onion, small</p> <p>2 tsp marjoram</p> <p>1 tsp mustard</p> <p>1 tsp smoked salt, alternatively regular salt</p> <p>1/2 tsp pepper</p> <p>2 tbsp vegetable oil, e.g. rapeseed oil</p>"},{"location":"savoury/kidney-bean-leberwurst-vegan.html#preparation","title":"Preparation","text":"<p>Finely dice the onion and saut'e in a pan with a dash of vegetable oil at medium temperature for  a few minutes. Add marjoram and sweat briefly. Remove from the heat and let cool down a bit.</p> <p>Drain the beans well. Roughly crumble the tofu. Mix with all the other ingredients in a food processor or with the help of a hand blender until the vegan liver sausage has the desired consistency. If necessary, add a few drops of water in the course of this.</p>"},{"location":"savoury/tahini-hummus.html","title":"Tahini-Hummus","text":""},{"location":"savoury/tahini-hummus.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>1 medium-large clove of garlic 110ml water 45ml lemon juice 250g tahini 480g chickpeas 1.5 tsp salt</p>"},{"location":"savoury/tahini-hummus.html#method","title":"Method","text":"<p>Pur\u00e9e all but the chickpeas first. Then add half the chickpeas and puree until smooth. Add the second half of chickpeas and puree until smooth or leave some coarseness.</p>"},{"location":"savoury/tahini-sauce.html","title":"Tahini sauce","text":"<p>For Lebanese recipes always use the light-coloured version and not the whole dark tahini.</p>"},{"location":"savoury/tahini-sauce.html#yield","title":"Yield","text":"<p>Makes 250ml.</p>"},{"location":"savoury/tahini-sauce.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>100g tahini 2 tbsp lemon juice 1 clove garlic, crushed 1/2 tsp salt About 100ml cold water</p>"},{"location":"savoury/tahini-sauce.html#preparation-time","title":"Preparation time","text":"<p>5 minutes</p>"},{"location":"savoury/vegan-mett.html","title":"Vegan Mett","text":""},{"location":"savoury/vegan-mett.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>100g rice cakes</p> <p>250-300ml water</p> <p>1/2-1 white onion</p> <p>50g tomato paste</p> <p>Salt &amp; pepper</p> <p>2 sprigs parsley</p> <p>4 white bread rolls</p>"},{"location":"savoury/vegan-mett.html#preparation","title":"Preparation","text":"<p>Crumble the rice cakes in a bowl with your fingers.</p> <p>Add the water and gradually fold in with a fork so that the water can distribute well. Let soak.</p> <p>Cut off the ends of the onions, remove the peel and dice the onion.</p> <p>Add diced onion and tomato paste to the soaked rice cake and fold in with a fork and distribute well.</p> <p>Season well with salt and pepper. Then let rest in the refrigerator for a few hours for best results.</p>"},{"location":"soup/carrot-soup.html","title":"Carrot soup (creamy Thai)","text":""},{"location":"soup/carrot-soup.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>1 Tbsp neutral oil</p> <p>250g onions, chopped</p> <p>1.5 Tbsp garlic, minced</p> <p>2 Tbsp ginger, minced</p> <p>650g carrots 1.5cm</p> <p>350g parsnip (or more carrot)</p> <p>1l broth, veg or (fake) chicken</p> <p>2 Tbsp soya sauce / tamari</p> <p>2 Tbsp vegetarian fish sauce</p> <p>0.5-1 Tbs sriracha </p> <p>50g creamed coconut (optional)</p> <p>250ml of orange juice</p> <p>2 Tbsp sugar</p>"},{"location":"soup/carrot-soup.html#method","title":"Method","text":"<p>Fry the onions until golden. Add garlic and ginger and fry for another minute. Add carrots and broth. Bring to a boil and simmer for 8 mins. Add parsnip cubes and simmer for another 18 minutes. Add sauces and sugar, blend smooth in high speed blender. Pour back into the pot and stir in orange juice.</p>"},{"location":"soup/french-lentil-soup.html","title":"French lentil soup smokey","text":"<p>Stove top or slow cooker </p>"},{"location":"soup/french-lentil-soup.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>1.5 Tbs olive oil</p> <p>450g minced (red) onions</p> <p>6 cloves minced garlic</p> <p>2 Tbsp thyme</p> <p>2 Tbsp smoked paprika</p> <p>2 Tbsp tomato pur\u00e9e</p> <p>1.5 tsp Dijon mustard </p> <p>600g carrots in thick slices</p> <p>3 cups French lentils (puy / green / brown)</p> <p>3 cups vegetable or (fake) chicken stock</p> <p>5 cups water</p> <p>2 bay leaves</p> <p>1.5 tsp salt</p> <p>2 Tbsp lemon juice</p>"},{"location":"soup/french-lentil-soup.html#method","title":"Method","text":"<p>Fry the onions until golden. Add the garlic and fry for a minute. Add thyme, smoked paprika, tomato pur\u00e9e and Dijon mustard, fry for another minute. Add vegetables stock and stir to dissolve residue stuck to the bottom of the pot. Transfer everything to the slow cooker. Add carrots, washed lentils, water, bay leaves and salt. Cook on high for 4h. Stove top method (simmering) requires 1h approximately.</p> <p>Add lemon juice and season to taste with more salt.</p>"},{"location":"soup/lemony-lentil.html","title":"Lemony Lentil &amp; Chard Soup","text":"<p>This satisfying lemony bowlful was inspired by the lentil soup served at the now-closed Lebanese restaurant La Shish in West Bloomfield, Michigan. It keeps well but will thicken, so you may want to thin it with a bit of water or broth when reheating. Serve with warm whole-wheat pita.</p>"},{"location":"soup/lemony-lentil.html#method","title":"Method","text":"<p>Active Time: 30 mins</p> <p>Total Time: 55 mins</p> <p>Servings: 6 </p>"},{"location":"soup/lemony-lentil.html#nutrition-profile","title":"Nutrition Profile","text":"<p>Mediterranean Diet Dairy-Free Soy-Free High-Fiber Vegan Vegetarian High-Protein Egg-Free Gluten-Free Low-Calorie</p>"},{"location":"soup/lemony-lentil.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>3 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil, plus more for serving</p> <p>1 large onion, diced</p> <p>1 bunch chard</p> <p>4 cloves garlic, finely chopped</p> <p>1 tablespoon ground cumin</p> <p>\u00bd teaspoon Aleppo pepper, plus more for serving</p> <p>8 cups water</p> <p>1 pound red lentils, picked over and rinsed</p> <p>1 \u00bd teaspoons salt</p>"},{"location":"sweet/frangipane.html","title":"Frangipane (Almond Cream)","text":"<p>Frangipane, a staple of classic French pastry, is a creamy, sweet, almondy filling that\u2019s surprisingly easy to make and has many uses. This frangipane recipe uses simple ingredients like butter, sugar, eggs, and almond flour to ensure the almond flavor shines through. Spread frangipane into a tart shell, pipe it into croissant dough to make a decadent breakfast pastry, or spread it onto brioche to make Bostock.</p>"},{"location":"sweet/frangipane.html#preparation","title":"Preparation","text":"<p>5 mins</p>"},{"location":"sweet/frangipane.html#total","title":"Total","text":"<p>5 mins</p>"},{"location":"sweet/frangipane.html#yield","title":"Yield","text":"<p>about 1 3/4 cups</p> <p>Frangipane (Almond Cream)</p>"},{"location":"sweet/frangipane.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>6 tablespoons (85g) unsalted butter, at room temperature 1/2 cup (99g) granulated sugar 1/4 teaspoon table salt 1 cup (96g) King Arthur Almond Flour 3 tablespoons (23g) King Arthur Unbleached All-Purpose Flour or King Arthur Gluten-Free Measure for Measure Flour 1 large egg, at room temperature 2 teaspoons almond emulsion or almond extract</p>"},{"location":"sweet/frangipane.html#instructions","title":"Instructions","text":"<p>In a medium bowl or the bowl of a stand mixer, beat together the butter, sugar, and salt until pale and fluffy, about 1 minute on medium speed.</p> <p>Stir in the flours, egg, and almond flavoring. Mix until just combined.</p> <p>Use the frangipane as desired: fill tart shells, pipe into croissant dough, top slices of Bostock, or come up with your own way to use this flavorful, nutty filling. Bake the frangipane as directed in your recipe or until it\u2019s golden brown and smells nutty.</p> <p>Store leftover unbaked frangipane in the refrigerator, covered, for up to 1 week or freeze for up to 2 months.</p>"},{"location":"sweet/peanut-butter-cookie-dough-bites.html","title":"Peanut butter cookie dough bites","text":""},{"location":"sweet/peanut-butter-cookie-dough-bites.html#ingredients","title":"Ingredients","text":"<p>150g gluten-free rolled oats</p> <p>2 tablespoons coconut oil</p> <p>2 tablespoons smooth peanut butter, almond butter or</p> <p>sunflower seed butter</p> <p>60ml pure maple syrup or other liquid sweetener</p> <p>1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract</p> <p>60g almond flour or almond meal</p> <p>\u00bc teaspoon fine-grain sea salt</p> <p>2 tablespoons mini dark chocolate chips or chopped dark</p> <p>chocolate</p>"},{"location":"sweet/peanut-butter-cookie-dough-bites.html#yield","title":"Yield","text":"<p>Makes 14 small bites</p>"},{"location":"sweet/peanut-butter-cookie-dough-bites.html#preparation","title":"Preparation","text":"<p>PREP TIME: 15 minutes</p> <p>CHILL TIME: 10 minutes</p>"},{"location":"sweet/peanut-butter-cookie-dough-bites.html#allergy-info","title":"Allergy info","text":"<p>gluten-free, raw/no-bake, soy-free option, nut-free option, refined sugar-free</p>"},{"location":"sweet/peanut-butter-cookie-dough-bites.html#instructions","title":"Instructions","text":"<p>In a high-speed blender, blend the oats until a fine flour forms. Set aside.</p> <p>In a large bowl, combine the oil, peanut butter, maple syrup, and vanilla and beat with a hand mixer until smooth. Add the almond flour, oat flour, and salt and beat again until combined. Fold in the chocolate chips.</p> <p>Roll the dough intc small balls (about 1 tablespoon of dough each). If chocolate chips fall to the bottom of the bowl, press them back into the dough when rolling. Place the fihished bites on a plate lined with parchment paper.</p> <p>Freeze the bites for 5 to 10 minutes, or until firm. Store the bites in the freezer in a freezer bag for quick and easy snacks.</p>"},{"location":"sweet/peanut-butter-cookie-dough-bites.html#tips","title":"Tips","text":"<p>For a nut-free version, simply swap sunflower seed butter for the peanut butter and more oat</p> <p>flour for the almond flour (add a splash of non-dairy milk if the dough is a bit dry). Both versions work just fine.</p> <p>For a soy-free option, use soy-free chocolate chips (such as Enjoy Life brand)</p> <p>[Liddon, Oh She Glows, S. 234]</p>"}]}